title: North Korea Test Launches Unknown Projectile, South Korean Military Says
sub_head: The Wednesday launch is North Korea’s 10th weapons test of the year
body:
SEOUL—North Korea test-fired an unknown projectile on Wednesday, though the launch was unsuccessful, South Korea’s military said.
The attempted launch occurred at 9:30 a.m. local time from the Sunan area, according to the South Korean military. The U.S. and South Korea are conducting further analysis, it added.
